headline: Here's How Many Shares of McDonald's Stock You Must Own to Get $5,000 in Yearly Dividends
summary: McDonald's stock has historically trounced the S&P 500, and its large dividend payouts are part of the reason.  Dividend stocks are ideal for retirees who prioritize passive income.  In the past, a good portion of equity investing was about dividends -- that nice chunk of cash public companies return to investors every quarter.
